From 203dcf5eaf2ec8ef2ad98075b97580bd9d22cec2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nikolai Zhukov <coderobjc@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 15 Jan 2026 12:40:03 +0400
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] fix(ToriiClient): use URL(string:relativeTo:) to prevent
 double percent-encoding
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The previous implementation using appendingPathComponent caused double
percent-encoding of special characters in path components (e.g., %40 → %2540).
This broke requests with account IDs like "alice@wonderland".

Changes:
- Normalize baseURL to directory URL in init (required for RFC 3986 compliance)
- Replace string concatenation with URL(string:relativeTo:) in makeRequest
- Update tests to verify absoluteString (URL.path always returns decoded path)
- Change transaction submit endpoint from /v1/pipeline/transactions to /transaction

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 .../Sources/IrohaSwift/ToriiClient.swift      | 34 ++++----
 .../IrohaSwiftTests/ToriiClientTests.swift    | 81 +++++++++++++------
 2 files changed, 75 insertions(+), 40 deletions(-)

